Key Match Events: The Dallas Mavericks ended their four-game losing streak by defeating the San Antonio Spurs, 110-93.
Kyrie Irving and Luka Doncic combined for 38 points.
Daniel Gafford top-scored for Dallas with 22 points and seven rebounds.
Gafford also threw down four alley-oop dunks.
Dallas scored 38 points in the third quarter compared to San Antonio's 18, marking the turning point in the game.
The Spurs pulled out all of their starters with five minutes remaining in the fourth quarter.
